Tested install on Ubuntu 14.04:

1.  mkdir powot_project
2.  cd powot_project
3.  git clone https://github.com/LubomirBogdanov/powot_simulator_v2.git
4.  Install Qt Creator Open Source on your local machine
5.  Import the Qt project that you've just cloned with the Qt Creator IDE --> powot_project/powot_simulator_v2/powot_simulator_project.pro
6.  gedit ~/.bashrc
7.  export PATH+=:/path/to/Qt/project/powot_simulator_v2/build-powot_simulator_project-Desktop_Qt_X_X_GCC_XXbit-Debug/powsimu
8.  export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}:/path/to/Qt/project/powot_simulator_v2/build-powot_simulator_project-Desktop_Qt_X_X_GCC_XXbit-Debug/powot_simulator
9.  source ~/.bashrc
10. cd /path/to/Qt/project/powot_simulator_v2/build-powot_simulator_project-Desktop_Qt_X_X_GCC_XXbit-Debug/powsimu

